        "from": "OrderService",
        "to": "InventoryService",
        "status": "risk",
        "issue": "1 retry on 3s timeout means OrderService can take up to 6s to respond. CartService gives OrderService only 5s. If the first InventoryService call times out at 3s and the retry takes >2s, CartService will timeout before OrderService finishes. Retry budget exceeds upstream timeout budget."
      },
      {
        "from": "PaymentService",
        "to": "PaymentGateway (external)",
        "status": "risk",
        "issue": "No circuit breaker on the external payment gateway. If the gateway is degraded (e.g., responding slowly at 7-8s), every checkout request will hang for 5s (CartService timeout), burning resources across all three services with no fast-fail."
      },
      {
        "from": "CartService",
        "to": "OrderService → PaymentService (sequence)",
        "status": "broken",
        "issue": "NO COMPENSATION/SAGA: CartService creates the order first, then charges payment. If PaymentService fails (timeout, circuit open, gateway error), the order is left in a created-but-unpaid state with no rollback. There is no compensating transaction to cancel the order or release reserved inventory."
      }
    ],
    "contract_compliance": "No mention of idempotency keys on any call. The payment gateway call is especially dangerous without idempotency — the timeout mismatch means CartService may retry the entire flow (at a higher level) causing duplicate charges. OrderService retry on InventoryService also needs idempotency to avoid double-reserving stock.",
    "data_flow_integrity": "Broken. The sequential call pattern (Order then Payment) without a saga or compensation mechanism guarantees data inconsistency on partial failures. Orders will exist without payments. Inventory will be reserved without completed checkouts. Over time this creates phantom orders and stuck inventory."
  },

  "observability_review": {
    "logging": {
      "coverage": "missing",
      "gaps": [
        "No structured logging mentioned for any service",
        "No correlation/request ID propagation across CartService → OrderService → PaymentService calls",
        "No logging of timeout events, circuit breaker state transitions, or retry attempts",
        "Ghost payment scenario (timeout mismatch) will be nearly impossible to debug without correlated logs"
      ]
    },
    "metrics": {
      "coverage": "missing",
      "gaps": [
        "No latency histograms (p50/p95/p99) on any inter-service call",
        "No error rate tracking per downstream dependency",
        "No circuit breaker state metric (open/closed/half-open) on PaymentService breaker",
        "No metric for orphaned orders (created but unpaid)",
        "No payment gateway success/failure/timeout rate",
        "No inventory reservation rate vs completion rate"
      ]
    },
    "tracing": {
      "coverage": "missing",
      "gaps": [
        "No distributed tracing across the 4-service call chain (Cart → Order → Inventory, Cart → Payment → Gateway)",
        "No span annotations for retry attempts or circuit breaker decisions",
        "Without tracing, the timeout mismatch between CartService (5s) and PaymentService (8s) will manifest as mysterious payment failures with no root cause visibility"
